caption: Really great meal with great service. Hidden gem of a place. Highly recommend.
the cocktail and food was amazing!

This place can be pretty hit or miss. Ordered tacos for takeout and they were great, but then got a burrito for dine in recently and it was kind of a rip off: I got the veggie burrito which was just filled with beans and rice, and came with a tiny side of undressed mixed salad greens.
Flavorful Chicken Fajitas!
Chorizo tacos + watermelon margs = 💘
Very good. Had tonadd some salt and pepper to the guacamole, but it was decent

Food was ok but felt ripped off. Margaritas were 9 dollars on menu .. was 12 on bill.. nachos were supposed to be 12 but on the bill it was  16.  I questioned the bill just to show I was bothered .. the waiter then came back after the fact and said I don’t need to leave a tip.  What ?!
Great Tacos and Chile Relleno
Friendly taqueria tucked into the quietest neighborhood corner. Low traffic and close to Fort Hamilton subway exit. Perfect for margaritas and tacos and for running into your dog walking neighbors.
On a chilly rainy still-pandemic night, Cena has given us a wonderful solo outside pod date with fabulous cocktails and food. Do you miss restaurants? This one is safe and highly recommended. 👏
Awesome covered outdoor seating setup. Delicious cocktails

Happy to have this spot in our neighborhood. Has adapted nicely to the horror show of running a restaurant during COVID. Staff may be young and have a little to learn but were nothing but nice to us. And when we let them know how thankful we were that they were there, the service got even better. So it's not Jean Georges - relax, have a few drinks and be happy you have an option during this shitshow.

This place looks super cute and I really want to love it because it’s so close to my apt, but I just can’t. The food and drinks are ok, but what’s really terrible about this place is the waitstaff, who are unprofessional and disorganized in every way possible. The one female server doesn’t wear a mask properly (not covering her nose), both male servers are dressed as though they rolled out of bed and came to work, and it appears that none of them are assigned tables so customers are constantly trying to get someone’s attention to place orders and/or check up on orders.  Our orders were messed up and/or forgotten about multiple times last night!  Shame on the owner/management for not running this place more smoothly, efficiently, and safely!
Food was on point. You can tell everything was home made. Ordered: Taquitos, Barbacoa tacos, Shrimp Tacos (shrimp was perfect), and a side of  Spanish rice. Will definitely be back soon.

The Server at the front taking the orders is very rude. Perhaps he was having a bad day, but transference is unappetizing. The Tortilla soup was much too salty; hard shell tacos were not an option. The french fries too oily. The Mexican Street Corn Salad was tasty! The server at the bar who brought our meals to the outdoors table was pleasant. He made the experience less awful. His smile was visible even behind his blue medical mask!

Great neighborhood spot that has worked hard to adopt in this new world for restaurants. The food is truly authentic, some of the best homemade guac and chips I've had, a variety of fresh tacos (I had the tinga pollo). Saw them putting up heat lamps in the outdoor seating area. Certainly worth the visit and your support!

This is a very nice place. It’s very cozy the seating area outside. My husband and I went here 2 times, one during lunch time and after around evening, sadly we would love to give it 5 stars however we are not sure if because of the restrictions right now they have lower their standards a little bit? The first time our tacos were barely warm( we had take out) The al pastor tacos were okay the best were the Barbacoa (beef as they have it in their menu) tacos. We decided to give them a second try and that’s why we went later in the day to eat at the restaurant however the quality was the same. Tacos were somewhat warm and my enchiladas had the tinga chicken which wasn’t bad but I am not used to having them like that. We will probably go again and give it a second chance. However the Margaritas are pretty good and also their Jamaica water and definitely try their esquites they where great!
I would give it zero stars if that was an option.

The Tacos are good and savory; the sauce could use more umph. Giving two stars because service was horrible. Dude was either stoned or just a massive d1ckhead. Muttering under his breath and then refusing to serve my gf a drink because she didn’t have a physical ID but had a picture on her phone (she’s 24 + 5’10). We really didn’t care about that because the frozen margaritas was literally frozen with terrible straws couldn’t even drink. Spent like 40 dollars in less than 15 minutes and just had a terrible time. This is a yuppie money trap for ppl that can’t cook at home or just want to feel extra 🙄  Note: this was afternoon service
Delicious
Really liked the tacos.
Good food. Nice outdoor seating arrangement.
Nice sized burritos, quesadillas are filling and Margaritas will rock you.
Such a great local spot in the neighborhood. Fresh watermelon margaritas, fish tacos, tasty guacamole, and amazing chile relleno.
Good chips
Great food, generous portions, cool staff. They are doing a great job with the outside dining and social distancing regulations. Drinks are great too.
Super cute spot for takeout/outdoor dining. Solid (sneaky) margaritas. My tacos were good, albeit slightly over done on the fish. However, would return.
Had a good experience in here with my son. The food came quick and the service is just excellent. Prices are convenient.

The food was just okay. The person who takes the orders could be nicer, I felt like a Millitary service not the place to relax and have some fun. Wouldn’t recommend my friends and wouldn’t come back by myself either.

This place looks really nice from outside and they took good measures of social distancing for dining but the food is just ok. We had fajitas, tacos, guacamole and margaritas. Fajitas looked and tasted like they were steamed not sizzled on the grill and the only spice was black pepper and salt. Guacamole was so mushed that it was hard to tell if it was freshly made or not the taste was also not definitive. Drinks were good and maybe this what they should be aiming for. It is a nice place to hangout I guess
Excellent place!. Delicious food and nice team. The best place in Brooklyn. Love it
Fantastic little restaurant, charming outdoor (Covid) seating and delicious food and drinks. Lovely servers.
Read enjoyed the food and the drinks. The outdoor seating is spacious and the service is superb. Definitely my new favorite spot in South slope. Love the branding as well.

So, we had the Brooklyn Commune for years and it was sad to to lose them to Connecticut but Cena has been a wonderful addition to the neighborhood.  Opening during a National Grid blackmail scheme, limiting their kitchen's ability, shortly followed by a 100 year pandemic, they are putting out some really good neighborhood Mexican food and drinks, under duress.  Patronize them, say hello to our favorite server, Oliver, and enjoy a meal and drink.  Help keep them in our neighborhood and honor their determination and hard work in their struggle to stay in business!
Their smoothies are great. And I am not really into smoothies
So good and delicious. Nice atmosphere, friendly staff.
Lovely Atmosphere with the new Outside seating.  The owner and Workers are a Joy very pleasant and friendly. The Nachos are Slamming
Best drinks and friendly staff.
It’s closed y’all. Their DoorDash is taking orders and their google maps says they are still open but they are closed.
Great neighborhood spot. Awesome staff, and the ambiance during the day is so bright,  fresh, and airy. Love that this is in our area.

LOVE this place and the owners! Food and service is amazing and we've thrown two private parties here that rank as our all-time favorite events. You can't go wrong with this place. And they're wonderful with kids and large parties. Beautiful interior as well with lots of light.

Amazing is all I can say! I’ve been coming to Cena regularly since they opened and it is truly a treat to have them in the area. Outstanding atmosphere and food plus a fun happy hour menu. Staff and service are so friendly and helpful. Would 100% recommend!

Amazing is all I can say! I’ve been coming to Cena regularly since they opened and it is truly a treat to have them in the area. Outstanding atmosphere and food plus a fun happy hour menu. Staff and service are so friendly and helpful. Would 100% recommend!
Casual Mexican, great for leisurely eating and drinking.
Food was great! Drinks could have been a tad better. Will come back for sure.

I had the fish taco and carne asade taco. Very generous portions, fresh ingredients, great flavor combinations. Kind and friendly staff, really well done interior making it feel airy and cozy at once.

Friendly efficient server, pleasant ambiance. It was nice that vegetarian chorizo was on the menu. My breakfast tacos were a little dull--not very spicy (even with chorizo and salsa), and all the ingredients had the same texture, nothing crunchy. So they didn't seem worth $12.
cool service, good beer, but food isn't exceptional
Oliver is the best. Great sopes too!
Great atmosphere, great staff, awesome food.

Charming and cozy Mexican eatery in Fort Hamilton.  The drinks are solid and services pretty quick. The menu is pricey, but it's in you restaurant and I'm sure they're being hit with sky-high rent. The tacos are a bit blend for my taste, but I'm from the Caribbean in like everything spicy. But it still good nonetheless and whenever I was in the neighborhood I grab something new from the menu and there has been no disappointment.

The space is very cozy, and all of our food was flavourful and tasty! The reason I'm only giving this three stars is due to the very small portion of food provided for the family-style tacos that were advertised as being for four people. The meal was also advertised as including sides of rice and beans, but as you can see in my picture, they were very small condiment sized portions. There was also not enough of the meat for four adults. However, the food itself was very good as previously stated. Our waiter was fairly unattentive as we had to physically get up and go find him to get drink refills and more tortillas.  This place has major potential and I'm hoping to return soon!
Excellent food and service!
Fajita
Excellent place, we really enjoyed the food! I loved the fish tacos! Nice people  and very good music!!
Awesome spot!
Excellent place, we really enjoyed the food! I loved the fish tacos! Nice people  and very good music!!
I just have to say this is one of the best Mexican restaurants around town. Honestly so glad I live by here ^_^

Great addition to the neighborhood.  Staff is always very chill, friendly, and knowledgeable. Music is on point. Juan is very helpful and provides a comfortable atmosphere for anytime. Breakfast is my fav. You can sit outside or enjoy the breeze from inside.
Great atmosphere. Great and friendly guys and the food to die for.
Beautiful space, kind service, delicious meal!

I have been very excited to try Cena as I'm always open to more taquerias in the neighborhood! Cena definitely stands out though. My wife and I just ate there and were both blown away by the service, food, drinks, and vibe. We have to recomend the chile relleño and the pescado taco. Insanely good stuff, and that's coming from two Texans as well! 😆 Cheers!
Great staff. Flavorful menu. Good beers on tap.
Everything was kinda bland.
We went for dinner and it was great. We had the burger and it was a great choice.

The gas is on! They have potential. Like others have said the chips are rock hard, they're also under salted. At least leave salt on the table. We ordered the small taco platter (for 4), which came with two sizable portions of meats and a tray of toppings - and FOUR tacos tortillas (they did bring more when asked). There was easily enough for 8-10 tacos. I wish there was a little more toppings, we ran out of creama pretty quickly, when asked for more they brought out a tablespoon worth. The kids meal, quesadilla, was actually a great value and looked great.  Service was quick, but pretty infrequent checks. Luckily it's a small space and you can stop them as they whisk by.  I'll go back in a few weeks.  Also nearly all the tables had "reserved" signs on them. And there were only 2 napkins at our table. At least bring a few more when the food comes, especially when there are kids.

Oliver and Juan are the perfect hosts in this Brooklyn bar.  The food and drinks are fab and the ambience is awesome We love you guys and if ever we are back in Brooklyn this would be our first stop 💞
Delicious tacos in a beautiful, light and airy space. Try the gorgeously lemony lemonade!
Excellent tacos (got al pastor and carnitas) and esquites. Haters on here being way harsh leaving one star reviews, got me scratching my head. Great vibe and great Mexican food! Will be back
Good clean and delicious..
Charming little place, food and service were both fantastics. Great spot to bring the family.
A needed spot for the neighborhood. Basic menu with good options for meat eaters. Enjoy all the fresh ingredients!
Cena is a wecome addition to the Windsor Terrace neighborhood but the food isn't unique enough for me to visit often when I can find better Mexican alternatives near me closer to Church ave.
Great breakfast tacos! We go every week!
(Translated by Google) A very quiet place and good food, excellent service  (Original) Un lugar muy tranquilo y buena comida, excelente atención

Went with our 2 sons to celebrate our anniversary and we loved it. I had gone in previously just to get guacamole and chips and I enjoyed it. My husband is a chef in the Hotel Trades Industry so he pays close attention to every  detail. The service was fast and very friendly. The food was delicious and presentation was on point. Servings were just right and ingredients were quite fresh. The only thing I would say is that the quesadilla was not cooked to the crispy texture I prefer and the sangria could use a little more fruit like peaches and grapes. Other than that, we loved it. We were in and out in about 1/2 hour which I loved. Our daughter had gone previously so we decided to stop in. Since we live down the block, we will definitely stop in again. Love that you can walk in and order to go too. I look forward to them expanding the menu a little in the future. Overall, great to have them in the neighborhood.

I was excited to try this place, it looks inviting, and is breezy and open. The service was pleasant and helpful, and I loved that they had a kid area with toys and books.  The homemade chips were extremely salty. We had to rub all of the salt off of them. The chicken tinga was pretty good, and I was excited to try the two vegetarian options, mushroom and rajas. Neither was great. Rajas taco was ok, but the mushroom taco really lacked flavor. We also got the steak bowl, which was very small, and the sour cream was on top of the tiny portion of meat, which made it hard to taste. We enjoyed the sangria, but it seems a little overpriced at $40/pitcher. Overall, very disappointing.
This place is amazing. Everything we ate was delicious, the service fast and friendly, and totally accommodating to my kid. Loved it and can't wait to be back in!
Great new spot in the hood. Check it out.

If you're a person of size or even slightly above average, don't expect a comfortable dining experience sitting on any of their tiny, awkward metal chairs. Even average size folks didn't look comfortable. Their only alternative is an equally uncomfortable booth and bench or sitting at their bar on bar stools with no back support.
Incredible Mexican food! Awesome drinks. Highly recommend the cilantro lemonade and the salsa trio. Staff is super friendly too.

I'm all about ambiance these days and Cena gets it right. From the tastefully decorated walls to the bright wide windows, Cena is a breath of fresh air and somewhere I will definitely return to. And don't get me started on the playlist. A wide variety that I knew couldn't be Pandora (everything from Tom Petty to Kjngs of Leon to old school Will Smith and Lil Flip), turned out to be one of the owner's playlists. The menu is simple but that's what they're going for.  We had a vegetarian burrito and the guacamole and both were satisfying. On top of it all, they have two of my favorite Brooklyn based IPAs: Merman NY IPA and Other Half's Green City. Can't wait until their alcohol license gets approved!
Tacos are amazing! But rice and beans are tasteless. Margarita was overpriced. Staff is very friendly and quick. Good atmosphere.
Amazing food!
Very chill spot!
Staff was so nice! Food, service, drinks, location... everything was amazing! 💜

I know Windsor Terrace is in dire need for a Taco place but Cena needs to up its game! The vibe and design are nice as is service, but I just don’t know how you screw up tacos... the food is mediocre at best. Rice and beans separate, seriously..? Sweet margarita mix and salty meat, burrito consisting of mainly rice...

This place is a welcome addition to the neighborhood. They’ve had some major challenges since they opened, including the gas being shut off in the entire building, but have handled it with grace and good humor. We have enjoyed all the food so far—really looking forward to the breakfast sandwiches!
I love this spot!

I was hopeful that there would be a new Mexican restaurant in the neighborhood that I could frequent, but left disappointed. Hard chips, a tiny serving of salsa, items on the menu not available and getting charged $13.00 for a Margarita that didn't seem to have any Tequila in it! Don't like to get ripped off like that! Won't be returning!
nice burrito and laid back vibe.

Love this place! The service was great, the vibe was chill. Had the tinga tostadas and few Pacifico’s. Great place if you’re looking for some good Mexican food during the weekend. Definitely would recommend if you’re in the neighborhood!
Amazing food at great prices.  Just what this neighborhood needed.

I was really excited tacos were coming to the neighborhood. This is my experience from last night's dinner. Upon arrival we were greeted immediately which was well appreciated. Unfortunately no server was in sight so the bartender took our order, also greatly appreciated but then was no where to be found when the place got busy because he was bartending. When asking a different server for help we were told they can't interfere with other people's already open checks, so my boyfriend had to walk to the bar every time we needed something. Quite annoying. The complimentary tortilla chips were as hard as a rock - after speaking to the server, he said their fryer broke & they had to buy their chips which made no sense because they were soaked in oil as if they just had fried them? So are you buying chips and then re frying them? Two out of the three tacos I ordered we're not available. I'm not quite sure how you sell out of your food at 8 pm on a Friday night which is prime dinner time! The tacos themselves were delicious however they only use 1 tortilla so as soon as you pick up the taco they fall apart in your hands and the juice is all over you; this could most likely be prevented if they doubled up on the tortillas. $13 for a margarita that barely has any liquor in it - calm down Cena, this isn't the W Hotel. One thing I did like was that they're using portable kiosks for payment but the server stood there and waited until we pulled out our money to pay on the spot instead of allowing the customers to decide how they want to pay amongst themselves. What if you're on a date for the first time with somebody ... you have to make this decision while someone is standing right in front of you? He should have left and came back in about a minute, it was very uncomfortable. I really hope that they take this post as helpful criticism. We will come back in a couple weeks to see if they have ironed out these kinks.

I understand that they have soft opening but prices are regular and service and food were horrible. Beans out of a can. Chips that almost broke our teeth. I will give them one more chance in about a month.
